18 1. $300,000 FOR AN INDIVIDUAL WHO IS AT LEAST 60
19 YEARS OLD AND:
20 A. IS A VETERAN, AS DEFINED IN § 9–901 OF THE STATE
21 GOVERNMENT ARTICLE; OR
22 B. HAS A DISABILITY CERTIFIED BY A LICENSED
23 PHYSICIAN THAT CAN REASONABLY BE EXPECTED TO LAST FOR A CONTINUOUS
24 PERIOD OF AT LEAST 12 MONTHS AFTER THE DATE ON WHICH THE PROCEEDING
25 BEGINS; AND
26 2. $150,000 FOR ANY OTHER INDIVIDUAL.
27 (III) IF MULTIPLE INDIVIDUALS IN THE SAME BANKRUPTCY
28 PROCEEDING CLAIM THE EXEMPTION UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I)2 OF THIS
29 PARAGRAPH FOR THE SAME PROPERTY, THE TOTAL EXEMPTION AMOUNT MAY NOT
